				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Eldrig guts<a name="75193"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 7 05 10:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Listen, it took me 3 months to find Elderig. Biggest piece of advice I can give you is to hang out around the druid port in. From there, you'd be able to track him if he's around. When I killed him it was me (59 bard at the time) and a 66 Druid. We killed him pretty quick, but I don't think you'd be able to solo him. Since he summons and takes away all of your buffs you wouldn't be able to solo him very easily. Biggest suggestion is just go in there, kill some of the mobs around the druid port for about an hour, then and wait around for him to spawn. After you get your guts, you'll feel alot better about yourself. Btw, I'm just 2 kills away from my Epic, and I haven't MQ'd a single thing. MQ'ing is great, but you'll really feel like you earned your epic once you get it without any MQ's!
<br />

<br />
Duke Reiden E. Firesong
<br />
Virtuoso of the 60th Hymn.
<br />
Cazic-Thule</span></td>
