				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The pathing listed it totally wrong, he follows the zone wall all the way around</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I can't speak for Eldrig himself, but his PHs definitely do <b>not</b> just follow the zone wall.  Come to think of it, I've run through the zone before (after my epic and didn't need him) and have seen him (Eldrig) near the wizard portal.  I wouldn't call that pathing &quot;following the zone wall&quot;.  I agree with you that the pathing information listed a couple of posts above isn't accurate either.
<br />

<br />
This is what I did...and I did it twice the same way (once for me and once for a friend):  I stationed my partner (yes, this will be <b>much</b> easier if you don't try to solo the hunt) at <b>EXACTLY</b> loc 564(pos), -4014(neg).  <b>Exactly</b> that loc.  I went everywhere between there and the the wizard portal area (and everywhere in between) and Highsunned everything I could find.  Within 30 mins, <b>both</b> times I did this, the PH got highsunned right on top of my partner's head.  My partner said that it scared the crap out of her both times she did it...just because it appeared right on top of her head.
<br />

<br />
Just be patient, bro, it will happen.  Once you find the PH, it's cake.  You'll just have to settle in for a normal camp then.  The camp is boring but easy once you have the PH.
<br />

<br />

